title: DOCS: Links to Source Code Broken
body_html:
When clicking the source links on the documentation page, the links leads to a non-existent pages.

eg, as a concrete example, from the following doc page:

  • http://pytorch.org/docs/data.html

The source link for the class torch.utils.data.Dataset links to the following page:

  • http://pytorch.org/docs/_modules/torch/utils/data/dataset.html#Dataset

body:
When clicking the `source` links on the documentation page, the links leads to a non-existent pages. 

eg, as a concrete example,  from the following doc page: 

- [http://pytorch.org/docs/data.html](http://pytorch.org/docs/data.html)

The `source` link for the `class torch.utils.data.Dataset` links to the following page:  

- [http://pytorch.org/docs/_modules/torch/utils/data/dataset.html#Dataset](http://pytorch.org/docs/_modules/torch/utils/data/dataset.html#Dataset)
